The Herald Business Reporter
PAN-African banking group, Ecobank Transactional Incorporated (ETI), the parent company to Ecobank Zimbabwe, says the adoption of digital services has enhanced business resilience amid the disruptive impact of Covid-19. With banking operations in 33 countries the group, which concluded its 32nd annual general meeting on Tuesday, said in a news release that digital products were proving to be a formidable path to sustainable business in the face of external shocks and pandemics such as Covid-19. Outgoing chairman, Mr Emmanuel Ikazoboh,Â  said the group has made strides in laying the foundation of achieving improved business and operational efficiency through adopting digital products with scalability, as well as strong corporate governance and continued expense discipline.